# THE PROJECT BRIEF #

# Project Name #

REAL‚ÄëTIME AI‚ÄëPOWERED TEXT‚ÄëTO‚Äë3D MODEL GENERATOR

# Product Description / Presentation #


REAL‚ÄëTIME AI‚ÄëPOWERED TEXT‚ÄëTO‚Äë3D MODEL GENERATOR ‚Äî Build Brief 

Project Codename: VoxelVerve ‚Ä¢ 

Product description / presentation
VoxelVerve is a real‚Äëtime text‚Äëto‚Äë3D creation studio. Designers describe an object (‚Äúbronze steampunk pocket watch with exposed gears‚Äù), and the system produces progressive previews (point cloud ‚Üí gaussian splats ‚Üí mesh) that refine into game‚Äëready, PBR‚Äëtextured models. A coordinated crew of agents (Planner, Geometry, Texture, QA, Optimizer, Exporter) manages the pipeline with human‚Äëin‚Äëthe‚Äëloop approvals.
What it does:
‚Ä¢	Parses natural‚Äëlanguage briefs into structured constraints (scale, units, topology, poly budget, texture sets, LODs).
‚Ä¢	Generates coarse geometry (implicit fields or splats) ‚Üí converts to watertight mesh ‚Üí unwraps UVs ‚Üí bakes PBR textures (albedo/normal/roughness/metallic/AO).
‚Ä¢	Streams interactive previews to the browser and supports live edits (prompt deltas, style refs, sculpt nudges, material tweaks).
‚Ä¢	Auto‚Äëoptimizes for realtime (decimation, LOD chain, Draco/meshopt compression) and export targets (GLB/gLTF/USDZ; optional FBX/OBJ).
‚Ä¢	Runs similarity/IP safety checks and produces a provenance bundle (seed, checkpoints, prompts, references, model versions).
Why 3D teams love it:
‚Ä¢	Sketch‚Äëto‚Äëasset in minutes with reproducible seeds and deterministic checkpoints.
‚Ä¢	Game/AR‚Äëready outputs that slot into modern pipelines (Unity/Unreal/WebGL/WebGPU) with consistent PBR packs and LODs.
‚Ä¢	Transparent safety & provenance so studios can ship with confidence.
Framework (and why)
LangGraph (agent orchestration) + LangChain (tools/RAG) + RAG (mandatory) with OpenAI + Claude. LangGraph gives deterministic, resumable, checkpointed flows with explicit human approval gates (mesh sign‚Äëoff, texture sign‚Äëoff, export sign‚Äëoff). LangChain unifies retrievers (stylebooks, reference libraries) and tool calling (geometry/UV/texture workers). RAG grounds decisions in user style guides, asset libraries, and naming/taxonomy rules. FE: Next.js 14 + React 18 + TypeScript + Tailwind + react‚Äëthree‚Äëfiber. BE: FastAPI + PostgreSQL + pgvector + Redis, plus GPU worker pods for geometry/texture tasks. Deploy: Vercel/Render (+ GPU runner).
1. BACKEND ARCHITECTURE (extensive)
‚Ä¢	Core Services: FastAPI (async), Python 3.11 preferred, SQLAlchemy 2.0 (async), Pydantic v2, Uvicorn/Gunicorn.
‚Ä¢	Auth & Tenancy: JWT access/refresh; optional SSO (OIDC/SAML); RBAC roles (owner/admin/artist/reviewer/automation); per‚Äëtenant buckets.
‚Ä¢	Data Model: tenants, users, projects, scenes, prompts, runs, checkpoints, meshes, materials, textures, LODs, UV maps, refs, citations, exports, audits.
‚Ä¢	Vector Store: pgvector for embeddings (stylebooks, ref images, taxonomy terms, prompt chunks); hybrid BM25+vector; recency + credibility scores.
‚Ä¢	RAG Corpus: user style guides, mood boards, shader libraries, topology/retopo guides; quotes/offsets and ‚Äúas‚Äëof‚Äù timestamps preserved.
‚Ä¢	Agent Graph (LangGraph): Plan ‚Üí CoarseGen (splat/SDF) ‚Üí MeshRecon ‚Üí UVUnwrap ‚Üí TextureBake ‚Üí QA & Safety ‚Üí Optimize ‚Üí Export ‚Üí Publish; checkpoints + HIL gates.
‚Ä¢	Geometry Pipelines: implicit field (SDF) or gaussian splatting to coarse geometry; marching cubes/dual contouring to mesh; remesh/retopo tools; watertightness & manifold checks.
‚Ä¢	UV & Textures: xatlas/OpenMesh/Trimesh helpers; UDIM optional; texture baking (albedo, normal, roughness, metallic, AO, emissive); denoise & seam‚Äëaware dilation.
‚Ä¢	Optimization: quadric decimation, LOD chain gen, tangent/bitangent calc, meshopt & Draco compression; glTF KHR_materials_* extensions support.
‚Ä¢	Similarity & IP Safety: chroma/geometry fingerprints, text‚Äëimage embedding distances vs. reference corpus; threshold policies and alternative suggestions.
‚Ä¢	Provenance: store seeds, model versions, steps, loss curves; attach tool outputs and citations; export provenance JSON in artifact.
‚Ä¢	Realtime: WebSockets for token/preview streaming (point cloud ‚Üí splat ‚Üí mesh); job progress & event bus updates to clients.
‚Ä¢	Jobs & Queues: Redis streams for generation, baking, optimization, exports; idempotent workers; DLQ; resumable checkpoints.
‚Ä¢	GPU Workers: dedicated containers with CUDA/cuDNN; PyTorch + Kaolin/PyTorch3D/Open3D; FFmpeg for texture packing; watchdog + autoscaling.
‚Ä¢	Storage: S3/GCS with signed URLs; WORM bucket for audit/provenance; lifecycle policies; checksum de‚Äëduplication; AV scanning on upload.
‚Ä¢	API Surface: REST endpoints for sessions/runs, prompts, refs, geometry ops, UV/texture ops, optimization, exports, citations, audits, admin.
‚Ä¢	Connectors: Asset sources (Google Drive/Dropbox/SharePoint), DCC interchange (Maya/Blender/Unreal/Unity via export webhooks), webhooks with HMAC & idempotency.
‚Ä¢	Email & Notifications: pipeline events, sign‚Äëoff requests, export links; templated emails; optional Slack/Teams webhooks.
‚Ä¢	Security: HMAC webhook verification; request signing between FE/BE/workers; rate limiting; secrets via KMS/Vault; CSP for preview endpoints.
‚Ä¢	Governance & Audit: append‚Äëonly audit logs of edits/approvals/exports; per‚Äëtenant retention; right‚Äëto‚Äëdelete for inputs; provenance bundle on every export.
2. FRONTEND ARCHITECTURE (extensive)
‚Ä¢	Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router), React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn/ui; react‚Äëthree‚Äëfiber + drei for scene graph.
‚Ä¢	Viewer: WebGL2/WebGPU renderer; HDRI lighting presets; orbit/fly cameras; gizmos (translate/rotate/scale); unit system & scale helpers.
‚Ä¢	Realtime Preview: progressive render pane (point cloud ‚Üí splats ‚Üí mesh); streaming updates via WebSockets; cancel/rollback controls.
‚Ä¢	Scene Graph Panel: objects/materials/LODs/UV sets; outliner with search; properties inspector with PBR preview and texture slots.
‚Ä¢	Prompt & Params: brief editor with style tokens; poly budget slider; topology constraints; UDIM toggle; export targets; seed control.
‚Ä¢	Material & Texture UI: channel packing (ORM/AO), tiling/offset, normal space, triplanar toggle; seam‚Äëaware preview; LUTs.
‚Ä¢	UV Workspace: unwrap preview, seam painting, texel density visualizer, UDIM tiles browser.
‚Ä¢	Safety & Provenance UI: similarity meters, policy warnings, citation panel; provenance bundle download before export.
‚Ä¢	Collaboration: multi‚Äëcursor presence, comments pinned to faces/regions, approvals for mesh/texture/export stages.
‚Ä¢	Internationalization & A11y: i18n; keyboard shortcuts for modeling tasks; high‚Äëcontrast & reduced‚Äëmotion modes; WCAG 2.1 AA.
‚Ä¢	Performance: code‚Äësplit editors, SSR for marketing pages, SPA for studio, workerized heavy UI ops (texture previews).
‚Ä¢	Exports: GLB/gLTF/USDZ (click‚Äëto‚ÄëAR on iOS), optional OBJ/FBX; drag‚Äëdrop to DCC; one‚Äëclick upload to Sketchfab (optional).
3. DESIGN REQUIREMENTS (UI/UX design based on product & industry)
‚Ä¢	Creation‚Äëfirst layout with left prompt pane, center 3D viewport, right inspector; bottom timeline for stages/checkpoints.
‚Ä¢	Neutral, studio‚Äëgrade color palette; subtle micro‚Äëinteractions (hover wireframe, seam highlight, gizmo snap hints).
‚Ä¢	Dark/light themes optimized for long sessions; type scale tuned for inspectors; focus states and status toasts for long jobs.
‚Ä¢	Clear affordances for scale/units, PBR channel meanings, and export targets to reduce mistakes.
4. CORE INTEGRATIONS
‚Ä¢	OpenAI + Claude via LangChain for planning, parameter extraction, and tool calling; structured JSON I/O for graph nodes.
‚Ä¢	RAG over style guides, shader docs, asset taxonomy, and customer ref libraries (pgvector).
‚Ä¢	3D Engines/Libs: PyTorch, Kaolin, PyTorch3D, Open3D, Trimesh, xatlas; FFmpeg for texture packing; meshopt/Draco for compression.
‚Ä¢	Cloud Storage: S3/GCS with signed URLs; email via SES/SendGrid; optional Slack/Teams for approvals.
5. DELIVERABLES REQUIRED
‚Ä¢	Next.js 14 studio: Viewer, Prompt & Params, Scene Graph, UV Workspace, Materials, Safety/Provenance, Approvals, Exports.
‚Ä¢	FastAPI backend with LangGraph pipeline, RAG services, GPU worker containers, similarity/IP safety checks, export service.
‚Ä¢	PostgreSQL schema + pgvector; ingestion pipelines; Alembic migrations; seed projects with genre/style templates.
‚Ä¢	WebSockets for progressive previews; audit logging; RBAC/SSO; webhook outbox; deployment configs and OpenAPI docs.
6. SUCCESS CRITERIA
‚Ä¢	E2E demo: prompt ‚Üí progressive preview ‚Üí mesh ‚Üí UV ‚Üí bake PBR ‚Üí optimize (LODs, compression) ‚Üí export GLB/USDZ with provenance bundle.
‚Ä¢	Meshes are manifold & watertight, meet poly budget, and pass viewer validation; textures are correct size/format and channel‚Äëpacked.
‚Ä¢	Similarity/IP safety scores below policy threshold or remediated with alternatives; citations and seeds included on export.
‚Ä¢	Outputs load in Unity/Unreal/Web/WebAR without material errors; optional auto‚Äëgenerated thumbnails and turntables.
7. IMPLEMENTATION GUIDELINES
‚Ä¢	Structured outputs everywhere. Core schema: {seed, units, scale, polyBudget, lods[], meshURI, uvSets[], textures{albedo,normal,roughness,metallic,ao,emissive}, provenance{models,steps,citations}, safety{similarity,flags}, export{targets[],draco?,meshopt?}}.
‚Ä¢	Deterministic graph with checkpoints and resumability; human gates before texture bake and export; dry‚Äërun mode in staging.
‚Ä¢	Prompt hygiene: sanitize inputs, block unsafe/illegal requests; respect stylebook constraints; explicit version pinning of models and DSP toolchains.
‚Ä¢	Reproducibility: persist seeds and random states; cache intermediates; idempotent workers; checksum artifacts; verify GLTF validator passes before release.
‚Ä¢	Streaming UX: send small preview geometries early (splat/point) and patch mesh deltas as refinement arrives.
8. SECURITY & COMPLIANCE
‚Ä¢	IP Safety: similarity checks vs. reference corpora; denylist sensitive brands/logos; provenance bundle with seeds and citations.
‚Ä¢	Data Protection: encryption at rest; signed URLs; least‚Äëprivilege IAM; secrets in KMS/Vault; audit access to exports.
‚Ä¢	Supply‚ÄëChain Safety: scan uploads for malicious GLTF/texture payloads; sandbox parsing; strict MIME checks; CSP on viewer endpoints.
‚Ä¢	User Controls: rights management on generated assets; license metadata tagging; retention + right‚Äëto‚Äëdelete for inputs.
Claude ‚Äî 5 critical prompts (prebuilt‚Äëarchitecture aware)
PROMPT 1 ‚Äî PROJECT SETUP & ARCHITECTURE
Extend the existing full‚Äëstack app without overwriting configs. FE: Next.js 14 (TS, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, react‚Äëthree‚Äëfiber, React Query). BE: FastAPI (async SQLAlchemy 2.0, Pydantic v2, JWT, RBAC). Data: PostgreSQL + pgvector, Redis. Add a LangGraph pipeline (Plan ‚Üí CoarseGen ‚Üí MeshRecon ‚Üí UVUnwrap ‚Üí TextureBake ‚Üí QA/Safety ‚Üí Optimize ‚Üí Export ‚Üí Publish) with HIL gates; provide env templates and Vercel/Render configs.

PROMPT 2 ‚Äî CORE BACKEND IMPLEMENTATION
Implement endpoints/services for prompts, runs, checkpoints, geometry (SDF/splats ‚Üí mesh), UV unwrap, texture bake, optimization (LODs, compression), similarity/IP safety, exports (GLB/gLTF/USDZ), WebSocket progress, provenance/audit logs, and connectors. Add idempotent GPU workers and outbox webhooks.

PROMPT 3 ‚Äî FRONTEND COMPONENTS & UI
Build Viewer (react‚Äëthree‚Äëfiber), Scene Graph/Inspector, UV Workspace, Materials editor, Prompt & Params panel, Safety/Provenance view, Approvals, and Exports. Maintain WCAG AA, keyboard bindings, progress toasts, and streaming preview from splats to mesh with cancel/rollback.

PROMPT 4 ‚Äî AI INTEGRATION & FEATURES
Integrate OpenAI + Claude via LangChain for planning/parameter extraction/tool calls; wire RAG over stylebooks and asset libraries. Enforce structured outputs, attach citations/provenance, run similarity/IP checks with threshold policies, and stream progressive geometry.

PROMPT 5 ‚Äî DEPLOYMENT & E2E DEMO
Provision DB/Redis, run migrations, seed demo projects (style guides, refs). Show end‚Äëto‚Äëend: prompt ‚Üí preview ‚Üí mesh ‚Üí UV ‚Üí bake ‚Üí optimize ‚Üí export GLB/USDZ with provenance. Output OpenAPI docs and sample cURL; preserve existing configs.





